OL,3,CMum calls for change after son died
OL,4,Cfrom choking on sensory ball
OL,6,FA mother is calling for change after
OL,7,Fher son died from choking on a soft
OL,8,Fsensory ball at a day centre for
OL,9,Fpeople with learning disabilities.
OL,11,FLouis Rawlinson, 27, was attending the
OL,12,Fday centre when he swallowed the
OL,13,Fsquidgy ball. An inquest recorded a
OL,14,Fconclusion of accidental death.
OL,16,FNow his mother, Andrea Buckley, has
OL,17,Flaunched a campaign calling for the
OL,18,Fballs to carry safety warning.
