OL,3,CMum calls for change after son died
OL,4,Cfrom choking on sensory ball
OL,6,FHis mother described him as "a proper
OL,7,Fcharacter" that was "full of
OL,8,Fpersonality" and a "wicked sense of
OL,9,Fhumour".
OL,11,FShe said: "My son had learning
OL,12,Fdisabilities and other health
OL,13,Fconditions and he attended a day
OL,14,Fcentre.
OL,16,F"Unfortunately on July 19 2023 he was
OL,17,Fplaying with his sensory toys like he
OL,18,Falways did and he choked on a sensory
OL,19,Fball that was one of his items that he
OL,20,Fplayed with."
