OL,3,CMum calls for change after son died
OL,4,Cfrom choking on sensory ball
OL,6,FThe ball was just under the size of a
OL,7,Ftennis ball, with beads inside that
OL,8,Fmade it malleable and easy for Louis
OL,9,Fto swallow.
OL,11,FAfter swallowing it, Louis suffered a
OL,12,Fcardiac arrest at the day centre
OL,13,Fbefore paramedics managed to get a
OL,14,Ftube in to give him some oxygen.
OL,16,FHowever, when he was at Fairfield
OL,17,FHospital in Bury, they realised the
OL,18,Fball had gone down his throat, on top
OL,19,Fhis vocal chords.
