OL,3,CMum calls for change after son died
OL,4,Cfrom choking on sensory ball
OL,6,F"I feel it's not just in Louis area
OL,7,Fthat is a concern all types of
OL,8,Fchildren have them as so readily
OL,9,Favailable and cheap.
OL,11,F"Louis had his for three years and it
OL,12,Fwas one of his favourite sensory items
OL,13,Fit just highlights how they can become
OL,14,Fso dangerous."
OL,16,FThe material of the ball means that it
OL,17,Fis easily compressed and made it
OL,18,Fdifficult for medical professionals to
OL,19,Frealise it was so far down Louis's
OL,20,Fthroat.
